1. install python 3.9 (windows 8 or later) 
2. install pip
3. in command prompt, write the following queries: 
	3a. pip install opencv-python
	3b. pip install mediapipe
	3c. pip install tensorflow
	3d. pip install numpy
	3e. pip install keras
4. record a mp4 / 3gp video and name it as input and save it in the same folder
5. run the source code to generate the output.mp4 video
